verbose_text: Because the phenotype observed in Stx6 depleted cells was found to be partly distinct from that for BAG6 knockdown (compare XREF_FIG B-c and XREF_FIG F-c in the absence of insulin, and XREF_FIG B-d and XREF_FIG F-d in the presence of insulin, respectively), we suggest that the defective synthesis of Stx6 might contribute, only in part, to the reduced cell surface expression of GLUT4 in BAG6 suppressed cells.
